cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CV

This paper discusses gradient estimators commonly used in machine and reinforcement learning, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on optimization and variance reduction suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the importance of these gradient estimators in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The mention of evolution strategies experiments suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY), and the potential application to a Beta distribution suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another possible sub-category.
